      <section class="experience">
        <h2 class="section-title" style="letter-spacing:0.18em;">WhatsApp API Automation</h2>

        <div class="experience-block">
          <div class="experience-role">WhatsApp Conversational Ordering Bot</div>
          <div class="experience-meta">Twilio WhatsApp API · Railway Deployment · Lightweight State Machine</div>
          <p class="muted">
            End-to-end conversational bot that automates customer order intake over WhatsApp: guided menu, free-text capture,
            validations, confirmation, and admin notifications. Built for a real small business use-case with a focus on
            reliability, clear UX, and operational continuity.
          </p>

          <div class="tag-row">
            <span class="tag">WhatsApp</span>
            <span class="tag">Twilio</span>
            <span class="tag">Webhook</span>
            <span class="tag">State Machine</span>
            <span class="tag">Railway</span>
            <span class="tag">Python</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="spacer"></div>

        <div class="experience-block">
          <div class="experience-company">What it does</div>
          <ul>
            <li>Guides users through an ordering flow (menu, quantities, delivery/pickup details).</li>
            <li>Accepts free-text messages and validates key fields (name, address, date/time, product, quantity).</li>
            <li>Confirms the final order and sends an admin notification to a personal WhatsApp number.</li>
            <li>Stores customer and order information in a database for follow-ups and operational tracking.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="experience-block">
          <div class="experience-company">Architecture</div>
          <ul>
            <li><b>Twilio WhatsApp</b> → inbound messages</li>
            <li><b>Webhook (Python)</b> → receives messages, routes by conversation state</li>
            <li><b>State machine</b> → controls steps, retries, fallbacks</li>
            <li><b>Database</b> → stores users, orders, and conversation state</li>
            <li><b>Admin notifier</b> → pushes confirmed orders to your admin WhatsApp</li>
            <li><b>Railway</b> → hosting/deployment</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="muted" style="margin-top:0.6rem;">
            TODO: Add your diagram/screenshot here, or describe your endpoints and env vars.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="experience-block">
          <div class="experience-company">Key features implemented</div>
          <ul>
            <li><b>Conversation state:</b> step-by-step flow with “back / retry” handling.</li>
            <li><b>Validations:</b> prevents incomplete orders (missing quantities, missing delivery info, etc.).</li>
            <li><b>Order confirmation:</b> user confirms before saving and notifying admin.</li>
            <li><b>Admin alerts:</b> sends the final order to your personal WhatsApp with a clear summary.</li>
            <li><b>Persistence:</b> stores customer info (“se guarda información del cliente”) + order history.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="experience-block">
          <div class="experience-company">Tech stack</div>
          <ul>
            <li>Python (Flask/FastAPI-style webhook)</li>
            <li>Twilio WhatsApp API</li>
            <li>Railway for deployment</li>
            <li>Database (TODO: Postgres/SQLite/etc.)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

